The Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC) Benue State command has disclosed that four persons have died in a road accident. The Sector Commander Yakubu Mohammed who confirmed this said the accident occurred on Thursday in Makurdi at 11:48 a.m. at the National Youth Service Corps (NYSC) Orientation Camp, Wannune, in Tarka Local Government Area of the state. According to him, 15 persons were injured in the accident. He said that both the injured and the dead had been taken to St. Christopher’s Hospital and NKST Hospital, both in Wannune. “Only one vehicle was involved, a Toyota Hiace which was conveying 19 people. “Out of the number 18 persons are females and one male adult. “The cause of the accident is speeding,” Mohammed said.